cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of estimating 3D human pose from 2D images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of weakly-supervised learning, which involves training on a combination of ground-truth 3D pose and ground-truth 2D pose. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses geometric constraints on skeleton pose to regularize the pose in 3D, which could place it in the category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of estimating human pose, which is a common topic in the field of multimedia, suggesting that it may also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
